# Astro UI Patterns

- Keep server logic in frontmatter. Use client-side JS only when interactivity requires it.
- Put reusable UI in `src/components/`; keep page-specific flow in `src/pages/`.
- Respect islands architecture and minimize `client:*` usage.
- All interactive controls need visible text or an `aria-label`.
- Inputs need matching `<label>` elements. Modals and dynamic UI need sensible focus handling.
- Use the shared `Icon` component and Feather-style icons. See `docs/IKONER.md`.
- Do not use emojis as UI icons and do not ship incomplete inline SVGs.
- Use the button classes from `src/styles/global.css`; do not redefine `.btn` styles inline.
- In admin pages that do not use `BaseLayout`, import `src/styles/global.css`.
- Back buttons should move one level up in the hierarchy, not jump to unrelated pages.
